{"author": "coding_agent", "parts": [{"text": "The task is complete. Here's a summary of what I did:\n\n1. **Inspected the raw bytes** of both `main.db` and `main.db-wal` before opening with SQLite (critical to avoid data loss).\n\n2. **Identified the corruption**: The WAL file was XOR-encrypted with the byte `0x42`. I confirmed this by XORing the first 4 bytes (`75 3d 44 c0`) with `0x42`, which produced `37 7f 06 82` \u2014 the exact SQLite WAL magic number.\n\n3. **Decrypted the WAL file** by XORing every byte with `0x42`, writing the result back to `main.db-wal`.\n\n4. **Queried the database** successfully, recovering all 11 records:\n   - The base database had 5 records (apple through elderberry, ids 1-5)\n   - The WAL contained 6 additional records (fig through mango, ids 6-11)\n\n5. **Created `/app/recovered.json`** with all 11 records sorted by id in the required format."}]}
